  "text": "Shi et al. [CITATION_1] proposes a model that stacks CNN with RNN to recognize scene text images. As illustrated in Fig.8 (a), CRNN consists of three parts: (1) convolutional layers, which extract a feature sequence from the input image; (2) recurrent layers, which predict a label distribution for each frame; (3) transcription layer (CTC layer), which translates the per-frame predictions into the final label sequence.",
